  "riddle": "1. Seek the pioneer of innovation in the world of music who has amassed numerous patents — how many can you uncover?\n\n2. Delve into the evolution of musical ensembles that have driven a rhythmic march forward; to which legendary military group does the history trace back?\n\n3. Unveil the name of the spirited woodwind often played in unison with drums, famed in many military and celebratory settings. How many tongues around the globe carry its name?\n\n4. What altitude does this land of melodies enjoy above the sea, where your previous discovery hails from?\n\n5. Nearby this melodic haven, how many green escapes exist, allowing for leisure and recreation?\n\n6. Now, seek the difference between the height you found in clue 4 and the nearby parks from clue 5. What is the absolute value of that computation?\n\n7. As you traverse the district surrounding this musical haven, how many places of exhibit can you find showcasing art and history?\n\n8. A dynamic ensemble emerged with a vibrant energy from the heart of Texas; what year marked its inception?\n\n9. In the domain of music education, during which century did a new teaching methodology, rooted in nurturing talent, first gain recognition?\n\n10. Within the realm of youth athletics, which organization oversees the rules and progressions of football at secondary schools across the nation?\n\n11. Upon discovering that governing body, note the value of its first character’s placement in the alphabet. What number corresponds to that letter?\n\n12. In the grand stadium where the local heroes play, how many spectators can be accommodated in its walls?\n\n13. Convert the height of the airplane runway ongoing since the 1920s to its length in feet. What is that transformed measurement?\n\n14. Reflection upon your conversion in clue 13 will reveal the wealth of binary data — how many 1s lie within its digital representation?\n\n15. To conclude your quest, calculate the absolute difference between the parks noted